    "text": "In this paper, we presented CaVulner , a novel approach for the precise identification of vulnerable versions in Java open source projects. CaVulner integrates multiple sources of information, including method level change patterns, CVE and CWE metadata, and patch diffs, with the semantic reasoning power of large language models. It localizes vulnerable code blocks, traces the commits that introduced those vulnerabilities and derives an accurate set of affected version tags by deduplicating hunk hashes and normalizing version labels. Our evaluation on 176 real-world CVEs from 43 projects covering 8,730 versions demonstrates that CaVulner outperforms state-of-the-art approaches, including V-SZZ, VERJava, and LLM4SZZ in accuracy, precision, recall, and F1-score. While this study focuses on the Java ecosystem, we will adapt CaVulner to additional language ecosystems such as C, C++, and Python in future work.",
